JOIN - Is used to combine ROW from two or more tables related to COLUMN 

INNER JOIN - only matching records in both table

SELECT e.Name , d.deptName
From Emp e 
Inner JOIN Dep d
ON e.DeptID = d.DeptID;

OUTER JOIN - returns both matching records and non-matching (include) will fill with NULL values for non match

SELECT e.Name , d.deptName
From Emp e 
OUTER JOIN Dep d
ON e.DeptID = d.DeptID;

LEFT JOIN (left outer join) - returns all rows from left table matching rows from right table 
               if not match null


SELECT e.Name , d.deptName
From Emp e (left)
LEFT JOIN Dep d (right)
ON e.DeptID = d.DeptID;

Ravi  IT
Anu   non
kumar desk
Meera Null
Rahul finance



RIGHT JOIN (right outer join) - returns all rows from right table matching rows from left table 
               if not match null

SELECT e.Name , d.deptName, 
From Emp e (left)
Right JOIN Dep d (right)
ON e.DeptID = d.DeptID;

Ravi  IT
Anu   non
kumar desk
Null  HR
Null  finance


FULL JOIN - Returns all records from both table. 

SELECT e.Name , d.deptName, 
From Emp e (left)
FULL JOIN Dep d (right)
ON e.DeptID = d.DeptID;

Ravi  IT
Anu   non
kumar desk
Meera Null
Rahul finance
Null  HR

CROSS JOIN - will not use* ( left X right ) 25 records - rows Cartesian product - every row X every row

SELF JOIN - join where the table joins with itself 


Emp - Manager 


SQL VIEWs

A sql View is a virtual based on result SELECT statement. 

That does not physical data stored in db.

CREATE VIEW view_name AS 
SELECT column 1, column 2, ...
FROM table_name
WHERE Conditon;

CREATE VIEW Company_view AS 
SELECT name, salary
FROM emp
WHERE Conditon = 'IT';


Select * From Company_view;


VIEW : read, reuse, securtiy

